{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase minimum and maximum penalties for taking a vehicle without consent",
        "additional_details": "Right now taking a vehicle without consent is a summary only offence. The maximum sentence is 6 months imprisonment, and the majority of cases are dealt with by Community Orders.\r\n\r\nWe want the maximum sentence to be increased to to at least 3 years imprisonment, and anyone convicted of this offence should receive a custodial sentence, and not a community order.",
        "background": "Due to the increase of vehicle theft offences, including vans with tools, we want the sentences for taking a vehicle without consent to be harsher.",
